       The module performs sunset/sunrise checks and refraction correction for
       sun position  calculation.  Local  coordinate  systems  are  internally
       transformed  to latitude/longitude for the SOLPOS algorithm. The eleva-
       tion is not considered in the sunset/sunrise calculations.

NNootteess
       r.sunmask and daylight savings: Rather than convert time  to  GMT,  the
       solpos algorithm uses what is called Local Standard Time, which is gen-
       erally defined politically as an offset from GMT.  So the  key  is  the
       offset  from  GMT,  which  the solpos Time Zone parameter.  If the user
       specifies clock time (different for winter and  summer),  he/she  would
       have  to  change the Time Zone parameter seasonally in r.sunmask (time-
       zone parameter).


       Note: In latitude/longitude locations  the  position  coordinates  pair
       (east/west)  has  to be specified in decimal degree (not D:M:S). If not
       specified, the map center's coordinates will be used.  Also _g_._r_e_g_i_o_n _-_l
       displays the map center's coordinates.

